# Variable is_docker is used by Jenkins. Jenkins tests provisioning by running
# it in a docker container. A docker container differs from virtualmachines.
# Certain things (iptables/cgroups) don't work. With "is_docker == true" can be
# checked if the deployment is rolled out to docker or not. If a task fails
# because of  docker, use "is_docker == true" to skip it.
# By default is_docker is false, jenkins overrides it and set is_docker = true.
